{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e596e805-4892-4b65-b530-d6c1996af4c7","content":"The main change is that Microsoft.Testing.Platform uses its own CLI flags, passed after `--`. Here's the mapping:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\nThe `--filter` syntax is unchanged. Everything after `--` is forwarded directly to the test runner host.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f57d33f-f318-4f90-b78c-7f46e76a511f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I can answer this directly without needing to explore the repository.\n\nLet me think about the key differences:\n\n1. **Filter**: `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` → `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` (same syntax works, but the MSTest runner uses `--filter` natively)\n\n2. **Logger**: `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (built-in TRX report generation)\n\n\n3. **Code coverage**: `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` (using the integrated Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n4. **Blame options**: `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`, `--blame-hang` becomes `--hangdump`, and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you either run the test executable directly or use `dotnet test` with these new command-line options.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test`, arguments after `--` get passed to the test runner itself, so you'd structure it as `dotnet test -- --filter \"Category=Integration\" --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura --crashdump --hangdump-timeout 5m`, or run the test project directly with `dotnet run --project <test.csproj> --` followed by the same options. Showing alternative approaches for running tests directly and clarifying that .NET 9+ has native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform in `dotnet test`, while .NET 8 requires additional configuration like setting the `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` property to enable compatibility mode. and you'll need to add the corresponding NuGet packages for each feature—`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for trx reporting, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage collection, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` for crash dumps, and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` for hang detection.","outputTokens":1601,"requestId":"E3CC:1ED62C:15C0B35:185EED3:6A05200E"},"id":"6eb6b6bd-c326-4825-8929-1519d4d54e4d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:46.563Z","parentId":"e32a4ffd-9384-405b-b48c-5c4e27fa53e6"}
